This paper deals with the problem of achieving multiple unicast capacity over a network, which involves information theory (cs.IT) and network infrastructure (cs.NI). The paper also discusses network topologies and capacity characterizations, which fall under the categories of distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC), social and information networks (cs.SI), and computational complexity (cs.CC).
